        { "@type": "Question", "name": "How often should you post to Google Business Profile?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Once a week, minimum. GBP posts expire after 7 days from the feed (event posts last until the event date), so weekly cadence keeps a fresh post visible. Twice a week is the sweet spot for active local businesses." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I schedule GBP posts for free?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — Publer's free plan includes GBP scheduling, as does Zoho Social's free tier. Google Business Profile itself does not have native scheduling. For done-for-you weekly posts that are written and designed for you, theStacc Local SEO at $49/mo handles the full pipeline." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the cheapest GBP posting tool?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Publer free or Zoho Social free for DIY. For paid, Localo at $29/mo and OneUp at $19/mo are the cheapest dedicated options. theStacc Local SEO ($49/mo) is the cheapest done-for-you option that writes and publishes for you weekly." }},
